      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_9hwRAc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>What is 9kt Gold? Your Complete Guide to Affordable Luxury</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_ygY8aG": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When exploring the world of fine jewelry, you'll encounter various gold purities. Among them, 9 karat gold stands out as a popular choice for its unique blend of beauty, durability, and affordability. But what is 9kt gold, really? At <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>, we believe in accessible luxury and transparent choices. This guide will demystify 9kt gold, helping you understand why this metal is a brilliant option for crafting modern, timeless pieces designed for everyday elegance especially when paired with our stunning lab grown diamond rings.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kKqW7n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Decoding 9kt Gold: The Basics of Purity and Composition",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Decoding 9kt Gold: The Basics of Purity and Composition</h2>",
            "custom_id": "decoding"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_yYFrht": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Decoding 9kt Gold:Paragraph ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Understanding what is 9kt gold starts with its composition. Unlike pure gold, which is too soft for jewelry, gold is mixed with other metals to create a stronger, more resilient alloy. The purity of this alloy is measured in karats (kt).</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Does the '9kt' Hallmark Actually Mean?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>What Does the '9kt' Hallmark Actually Mean?</h3>",
            "custom_id": "what-does"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_AynJ8F": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/2_4eeb2d8a-aaae-4327-a64d-c9f95bbd72f7.jpg",
            "text": "<p>The 15 parts of other metals, or alloys, are crucial. They not only provide strength but also influence the gold's final color. Common alloys include:<br/>1]Copper: Adds durability and a warm, rosy hue.<br/>2]Silver: Contributes to strength and can create a paler yellow or white gold.<br/>3]Zinc: Used to enhance durability and prevent tarnishing.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_DdEAth": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Does the '9kt' Hallmark Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>By adjusting the proportions of these metals, jewelers can create different shades like yellow, white, and rose gold offering a versatile palette for every design.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_eiqXmT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Great Debate: Is 9kt Gold Good for Your Jewelry Collection?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Great Debate: Is 9kt Gold Good for Your Jewelry Collection?</h2><p>One of the most common questions we hear is, <em>“Is 9kt gold good for jewelry?”</em> The answer is a resounding yes, particularly for those who value both practicality and elegance. It strikes an excellent balance between luxury and everyday wearability.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-great"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_eJghfD": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Case for Durability and Affordability",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>The Case for Durability and Affordability</h3><p>The higher alloy content makes 9kt gold incredibly durable. Here’s why it’s a smart choice</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_dKntWy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Case for  Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<ul><li>Superior Strength: It is significantly harder and more resistant to scratches and dents compared to 18kt or 22kt gold.<br/><br/></li><li>Perfect for Everyday Wear: Its robustness makes it ideal for pieces you wear daily, like engagement rings, delicate pendants, and bracelets.<br/><br/></li><li>Accessible Luxury: The lower pure gold content makes the price of 9kt gold much more accessible, allowing you to own beautifully crafted fine jewelry without a hefty price tag. To make it even easier, Lucira’s <em>Vault Of Dreams</em> savings plan helps you plan your purchase smartly.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_heze3G": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Considerations for Sensitive Skin and Long-Term Value",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Considerations for Sensitive Skin and Long-Term Value</h3><p>While the higher alloy content is great for durability, some people with very sensitive skin might be concerned about potential reactions. However, Lucira Jewelry mitigates this by using high-quality, often nickel-free alloys to ensure comfort. The long-term value of 9kt gold lies not just in its gold content but in its longevity and craftsmanship. When asking if 9kt gold is good, consider its lasting power as a piece you can wear and cherish for years.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QjmeLx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Appearance, Colour, and Durability: A Closer Look",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Appearance, Colour, and Durability: A Closer Look</h2>",
            "custom_id": "appearance"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_XTe3J3": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Appearance, Colour, and Durability Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Understanding the visual and physical properties of 9kt gold helps in making an informed decision. Let's explore the signature look of 9kt yellow gold and tackle the common concern about tarnishing.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_YWCtVp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What is 9kt Yellow Gold and Its Signature Hue?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>What is 9kt Yellow Gold and Its Signature Hue?</h3><p>So, what is 9kt yellow gold specifically? Its appearance is a beautiful, subtle pale yellow. This delicate hue is less intense than the deep, rich yellow of higher karats, which many find more versatile and modern. Its softer color complements a wide range of skin tones and pairs exquisitely with the brilliant sparkle of Lucira’s <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">modern diamond earrings design </span>creating a refined look perfect for any occasion.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_XTLqEm": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Does 9kt Gold Tarnish and How to Prevent It?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Does 9kt Gold Tarnish and How to Prevent It?</h3><p>A key question for many is, <em>does 9kt gold tarnish?</em> Pure gold itself does not tarnish. However, the alloy metals, particularly copper, can react with oxygen and moisture over time, which may cause slight discoloration or tarnish. The good news is that this is a very slow process and is easily managed.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_3fBN74": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion - The Final Lucira Tip",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Conclusion: Your Yes, Your forever </h2><p>Choosing an engagement ring is both emotional and practical, a mix of instinct and intention. The right one won't just look beautiful; it will feel like home.</p><p>Whether it's the confidence of the radiant solitaire, the modern geometry of the princess cut or the tenderness of the heart shaped ring, each piece in Lucira Jewelry’s collection is designed to capture one thing, that perfect unforgettable yes.</p>",
            "custom_id": "conclusion"
          }
        }
      },
